# kanshi — output layout profiles for grindstation
# Why this exists: see ~/Documents/SCREEN.md  ("Display persistence (kanshi)").
#
# kanshi applies the first profile whose listed outputs are all connected,
# so profiles are ordered most-specific (most outputs) first.
#
# TWO docks exist (see SCREEN.md "Docks"):
#   - OLD desk dock: external panels on DP-2 (Intel) + HDMI-A-1 (NVIDIA).
#   - NEW HP USB-C Dock G5: BOTH external panels land on the Intel iGPU as
#     DP-7 + DP-8 (plain USB-C DP-alt, NOT Thunderbolt). It drives both DP
#     ports at once, but eDP + DP-7 + DP-8 = three Intel outputs, so eDP is
#     capped at 240Hz (300Hz blows the iGPU budget and the panel modeset
#     silently loses — same failure as the old dock, just one output worse).
#     A transient "PHY A failed to request refclk" on each eDP modeset is
#     expected and recovers; a hard fail shows as eDP power=False.
#
# Monitors are matched by CONNECTOR (DP-2 / HDMI-A-1), not serial. The two
# MSI panels are the same model and differ only by serial, and serial-based
# matching backfired: a 2026-06-01 office move swapped the panels between the
# DP and HDMI ports, so the serial rules rotated/placed the wrong physical
# screen. Connector matching encodes the actual intent — "whatever's plugged
# into the DP port goes left-rotated" — and is stable for a fixed desk dock.
#   - DP-2     = Intel iGPU, DisplayPort over USB-C (left, portrait)
#   - HDMI-A-1 = NVIDIA HDMI (right)
# (Panel serials seen 2026-06-01: DP-2=CC2HM54A00885, HDMI-A-1=CC2HM54A00621.)
#
# Coordinate notes for the docked profile:
#   - DP-2 is portrait (logical 1440x2560), placed LEFT of the laptop
#     panel, occupying x[0..1440]. NOTE: the directive below says
#     `transform 270`, NOT a typo — kanshi's 90/270 land swapped vs sway's
#     reporting, so config `270` produces sway on-screen `transform 90`,
#     which is the right-side-up orientation. (Verified 2026-05-26.)
#   - eDP-2 (scale 1.3 -> logical 1969x1231) and HDMI (1.0 -> 2560x1440)
#     are vertically centred against DP-2's 2560px height.
#   - eDP-2 is capped at 240Hz when docked. 300Hz + a second Intel output
#     exceeds the iGPU's display-bandwidth/CDCLK budget, and the panel's
#     modeset silently loses (sway reports success, kernel refuses).
#     Undocked profiles restore the full 300Hz.

# OLD desk dock triple. Matched by CONNECTOR. This MUST stay listed before
# hp-dock-triple: that profile matches the two MSI panels by serial regardless
# of connector and would otherwise also match this dock — but the old desk
# mount needs a DIFFERENT rotation (sway 90 vs the HP dock's sway 270). The
# NVIDIA HDMI-A-1 output below is exposed ONLY by the old dock (the HP dock
# puts both panels on the Intel iGPU), so requiring it here cleanly fences the
# two docks apart.
profile docked-triple {
    output DP-2 enable mode 2560x1440@60Hz transform 270 scale 1 position 0,0
    output eDP-2 enable mode 2560x1600@240Hz scale 1.3 position 1440,665
    output HDMI-A-1 enable mode 2560x1440@144Hz scale 1 position 3409,560
}

# NEW HP USB-C Dock G5 triple. Matched by PANEL SERIAL, not connector: this
# dock's DP connector numbers are NOT stable — seen as DP-7/DP-8 on 2026-06-26,
# DP-9/DP-10 on 2026-06-29. Connector-based matching (the old DP-7/DP-8 rule)
# then matched nothing, kanshi fell through to `mobile` (eDP@300) and BLANKED
# the laptop panel. `man 5 kanshi` explicitly warns USB-C dock output names are
# unstable. Serials are stable; left=…885 / right=…621 has held across both docks.
#   - …885 = portrait panel, LEFT. Mounted FLIPPED 180° vs the old desk dock,
#     so right-side-up = sway on-screen transform 270 = kanshi config
#     `transform 90` (the documented 90<->270 swap). VERIFIED 2026-06-26 and
#     re-verified 2026-06-29. If it ever comes up upside-down, swap to 270.
#   - …621 = landscape panel, RIGHT, no rotation (kanshi normal = sway normal).
#   - eDP-2 capped at 240Hz (see header).
#   - Fallback if this still misfires: ~/.local/bin/hp-dock-layout.sh
profile hp-dock-triple {
    output "Microstep MAG 274QRFW CC2HM54A00885" enable mode 2560x1440@60Hz transform 90 scale 1 position 0,0
    output eDP-2 enable mode 2560x1600@240Hz scale 1.3 position 1440,665
    output "Microstep MAG 274QRFW CC2HM54A00621" enable mode 2560x1440@60Hz transform normal scale 1 position 3409,560
}

profile desk-dual {
    output eDP-2 enable mode 2560x1600@300Hz scale 1.3 position 0,107
    output HDMI-A-1 enable mode 2560x1440@144Hz scale 1 position 1969,0
}

profile mobile {
    output eDP-2 enable mode 2560x1600@300Hz scale 1.3 position 0,0
}
